WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.180
CHAPTER XVII.

00:08.280 --> 00:16.520
Better is a dry morsel, and quietness therewith, than a house full of sacrifices with strife.

00:17.680 --> 00:23.560
A wise servant shall have rule over a son that causeth shame, and shall have part of

00:23.560 --> 00:25.220
the inheritance among the brethren.

00:25.760 --> 00:32.280
The finding pot is for silver, and the furnace for gold, but the Lord trieth the hearts.

00:33.500 --> 00:39.560
A wicked doer giveth heed to false lips, and a liar giveth ear to a naughty tongue.

00:40.560 --> 00:48.460
Whoso mocketh the poor reproacheth his Maker, and he that is glad at calamities shall not be unpunished.

00:49.400 --> 00:55.600
Children's children are the crown of old men, and the glory of children are their fathers.

00:56.200 --> 01:01.880
Excellent speech becomeeth not a fool, much less do lying lips a prince.

01:03.320 --> 01:08.300
A gift is as a precious stone in the eyes of him that hath it, whithersoever it turneth,

01:08.480 --> 01:15.640
it prospereth. He that covereth a transgression seeketh love, but he that repeateth a matter

01:15.640 --> 01:23.700
separeth very friends. A reprooth entereth more into a wise man than a hundred stripes into a fool.

01:24.540 --> 01:30.400
An evil man seeketh only rebellion, therefore a cruel messenger shall be sent against him.

01:31.680 --> 01:36.820
Let a bear robbed of her whelps meet a man rather than a fool in his folly.

01:37.620 --> 01:42.060
Whoso rewardeth evil for good, evil shall not depart from his house.

01:42.780 --> 01:49.620
The beginning of strife is as when one leadeth out water, therefore leave off contention before it be

01:49.620 --> 01:56.740
meddled with. He that justifieth the wicked, and he that condemneth the just, even they both are

01:56.740 --> 02:02.680
abomination to the Lord. Wherefore is there a price in the hand of a fool to get wisdom,

02:02.940 --> 02:11.000
seeing he hath no heart to it? A friend loveth at all times, and a brother is born for adversity.

02:12.060 --> 02:17.960
A man void of understanding striketh hands, and becomeeth surety in the presence of his friend.

02:18.780 --> 02:24.820
He loveth transgression that loveth strife, and he that exalteth his gait seeketh destruction.

02:26.500 --> 02:33.160
He that hath a foward heart findeth no good, and he that hath a perverse tongue falleth into mischief.

02:33.760 --> 02:39.460
He that begetteth a fool doeth it to his sorrow, and the father of a fool hath no joy.

02:40.100 --> 02:45.460
A merry heart doeth good like a medicine, but a broken spirit dryeth the bones.

02:46.540 --> 02:51.100
A wicked man taketh a gift out of the bosom to pervert the ways of judgment.

02:52.140 --> 02:57.760
Wisdom is before him that hath understanding, but the eyes of a fool are in the ends of the earth.

02:58.780 --> 03:05.480
A foolish son is a grief to his father, and bitterness to her that bear him. Also to punish

03:05.480 --> 03:13.020
the just is not good, nor to strike princes for equity. He that hath knowledge spareth his words,

03:13.540 --> 03:19.920
and a man of understanding is of an excellent spirit. Even a fool when he holdeth his peace

03:19.920 --> 03:25.720
is counted wise, and he that shutteth his lips is esteemed a man of understanding.

